item.title: Java.class Help please!
item.dc:creator: @jc22493 Jc22493
item.description:
@jc22493 wrote:

The ‘messed up numbers’ and ‘icky words’ are called bytecode, which is a result of compiling the .java files. The information in the .class files can be read through the .java files.
